<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve McKinney, 37, a daredevil who skied at more than 100 m.p.h. and once flew 
a hang glider off Mount Everest, was killed when the stranded car in which he 
was sleeping was struck by another vehicle near Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators said that McKinney's car apparently suffered mechanical trouble 
on Interstate 5 early Saturday and McKinney had climbed onto the back seat to 
sleep before seeking help. 
</P>
<P>
One of his sisters is Tamara McKinney, a former Olympic gold medalist for the 
United States. 
</P>
