<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: TOREROS PASSED OVER FOR PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM LINDGREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite winning its final three football games on the road and finishing 7-2 
for the second year in a row, the University of San Diego was not selected to 
participate in the NCAA Division III playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Of 288 schools, only 16 are selected. 
</P>
<P>
With big victories over Azusa Pacific, 21-10, and Menlo College, 28-14, in 
their last two games, the Toreros were under consideration for their first 
berth since 1973. Redlands, which defeated USD, 28-14, earlier in the year, 
finished 8-1 and was the only West Coast school to make the playoffs, which 
begin Saturday. JIM LINDGREN 
</P>
</TEXT>
