<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROMANIA PARLIAMENT EXTENDS GOVERNMENT RULE OVER ECONOMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUCHAREST, Romania 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parliament empowered the Romanian government Monday to rule the economy by 
decree and speed up reforms aimed at building a free-market system after four 
decades of communism. 
</P>
<P>
Both chambers of Parliament voted by an overwhelming majority to give Prime 
Minister Petre Roman special powers. Roman had requested them in a report on 
the economic reforms he presented to Parliament Oct. 18. 
</P>
<P>
He had demanded a free hand to declare emergency economic measures over the 
next six months. 
</P>
<P>
This includes the power to change taxes and duties and to negotiate foreign 
credits without referring to Parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
