<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: GM ADDS TWO WEEKS TO VAN NUYS PLANT SHUTDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Motors Corp. extended its temporary shutdown of its Van Nuys assembly 
plant by two weeks because of sluggish sales. 
</P>
<P>
The plant, which employs about 3,500 hourly workers, will resume production 
Dec. 3 instead of Nov. 19, as originally planned. The facility, where GM builds 
the Chevrolet Camaro and Pontiac Firebird sports cars, has been closed since 
Nov. 5. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys is one of 11 U.S. assembly plants that are being temporarily idled by 
GM under a plan announced Oct. 31. 
</P>
