<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ST. IVES LABS' PROFIT UP 42% IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Ives Laboratories Inc., recovering from a marketing goof, said its 
third-quarter profit jumped 42% from a year earlier on a 9% increase in sales. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter ended Sept. 30, St. Ives' net income rose to $835,731 from 
$590,532 a year earlier, and its sales rose to $27.5 million from $25.3 
million. 
</P>
<P>
Based in Chatsworth, St. Ives makes shampoos and other personal-care products. 
In late-1989 and early this year, its earnings had slumped largely because the 
company had put its hair-care products in new packages that bombed with 
consumers. St. Ives has since gone back to its previous packaging and its 
profit rebounded in the latest quarter. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of 1990, however, St. Ives' profit was still down 33% 
from a year earlier, to $2.47 million from $3.71 million. Its nine-month sales 
fell 6% to $78.6 million from $83.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
