<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: STORAGE PROPERTIES POSTS $690,000 QUARTERLY INCOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Storage Properties Inc., a real estate investment trust that invests primarily 
in self-storage warehouses, reported net income of $690,000 on revenue of 
$790,000 in the third quarter ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
There are no comparable year-earlier figures, because Storage Properties began 
operations on Sept. 12, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
The publicly held company is headed by B. Wayne Hughes, who is also chairman of 
Public Storage Inc., a major operator of self-storage facilities. 
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of 1990, Storage Properties earned $1.80 million on 
revenue of $2.06 million. 
</P>
<P>
Separately, Storage Properties' directors also authorized the company to buy 
back up to 200,000 of its common shares in periodic open-market purchases. 
Storage Properties completed its initial public stock offering only a few weeks 
ago. 
</P>
