<TEXT>
<P>
The World League of American Football might not get started on schedule next 
spring because of the economy, NFL Commissioner Paul Tagliabue said. 
</P>
<P>
"Today there are a lot of uncertainties," Tagliabue said on the eve of a 
meeting of NFL owners. "The economy isn't as robust as it was when the idea of 
the league was launched." 
