<P>
Photo, COLOR, Honoring the County's War Dead: Eight-hundred American flags were 
raised Monday for a brief Veterans Day ceremony in memory of war veterans 
buried at Memory Garden Memorial Park and Mortuary in Brea. The tradition, 
which began with just six flags in 1957, was sponsored by veterans groups from 
Brea, Placentia and Fullerton, including the American Legion and Veterans of 
Foreign Wars. The flags are the original burial flags donated by each veteran's 
family. They are flown twice a year on Veterans Day and Memorial Day. There are 
more than 1,400 veterans buried in the park. Most of whom fought in World War I 
or II. KEN HIVELY / Los Angeles Times 
