<TEXT>
<P>
An elderly Chula Vista man died after being hit by a car Monday while crossing 
a street in Chula Vista, police said. 
</P>
<P>
John Garza, 82, was crossing 4th Avenue at Park Way about 10:20 a.m. when he 
was hit by a car driven by Edward Hurley, 76, also of Chula Vista, officers 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Taken to UC San Diego Medical Center, Garza died at 2:05 p.m., officers said. 
</P>
<P>
Hurley was not hurt, police said, adding that it had not been determined 
whether he would face criminal charges in the death. 
