<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DEPUTY KILLS MAN WHO ALLEGEDLY PULLED GUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A sheriff's deputy in Carson shot and fatally wounded a man in a motel room 
early Monday after the man pointed a gun at the deputy, sheriff's officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Todd Grayson, 26, of Carson was struck once in the chest about 1 a.m. at the 
Dare-U-Inn in the 17300 block of South Main Street, said Sgt. Robert Stoneman. 
</P>
<P>
Grayson was taken to Harbor-UCLA Medical Center, where he died. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's officials said that two deputies, who were not identified, were on 
foot patrol when they heard loud noises from a motel room. As they walked past 
the room, three people came out. Grayson stood in the doorway. 
</P>
<P>
When deputies asked if everything was all right, Grayson went into the room, 
pulled out a handgun and pointed it toward the deputies, Stoneman said. One 
deputy fired twice. 
</P>
<P>
Stoneman said Grayson had no criminal record and that there did not appear to 
be anything illegal going on in the room. The deputies told investigators they 
did not know why Grayson drew his gun. 
</P>
