</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies detained the driver of a van and 17 illegal aliens crammed 
inside, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The illegal immigrants were discovered Monday when Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
deputies, acting on a tip, searched the vehicle at a gas station in the Pico 
Rivera area, southeast of downtown Los Angeles, said Sgt. Michael Herek. 
</P>
<P>
The passengers and the driver were turned over to Immigration and 
Naturalization Service agents, said Herek. 
</P>
<P>
