<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OJAI; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL TO WEIGH BAN ON ALCOHOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THIA BELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ojai officials will consider a ban on alcohol consumption in all public parks 
and on city sidewalks. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council will discuss the request tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's Lt. Larry Weimer said he is seeking the ban on alcohol because 
drinking by adults at Little League games has been a problem for years. 
</P>
<P>
Weimer said several fights among rowdy fans and minor accidents involving drunk 
drivers prompted his request, along with continuing problems in enforcing a 
vague city law. The law prohibits drinking on public roads and in parking lots 
but does not mention sidewalks. One bleacher at Sarzotti Park actually occupies 
a sidewalk. 
</P>
<P>
Weimer, who serves as the city's police chief, wants the law to be clearer and 
to contain a section making it illegal to drink alcohol in any city park 
without a special permit. Event sponsors would apply to the city to obtain a 
permit. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager Andy Belknap is recommending that the matter be referred to the 
city's Parks and Recreation Commission for further review and public hearings. 
THIA BELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
