<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Art Imitating Life: A scene in "Rocky V" between Sylvester Stallone and his 
neophyte-actor son, 14-year-old Sage, may be left on the cutting-room floor 
because it came too close to real life, Stallone told Redbook. 
</P>
<P>
Stallone and his first wife, Sasha, divorced in 1985 and Sage and his brother 
Seargeoh, 11, remained with their mother. In the scene, Rocky tells his son 
"that no matter what, I'll never desert him," Stallone said. "I really lost it 
in that scene. Then Sage started to lose it because he'd never seen his father 
cry. It was all hitting too close to home, and I may take it out of the movie 
because it's just too emotional." CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
