MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nelson's Goods on the Road: Willie Nelson's real estate holdings, including his 
golf course and recording studio, were padlocked Monday after the Internal 
Revenue Service seized the country singer's properties in six states to satisfy 
$6.5 million in back taxes. The actions were taken less than two months after 
the IRS placed $16.7 million in liens on Nelson's real estate holdings and 
personal property. The order applies to Nelson's property in Texas, Alabama, 
California, Colorado, Hawaii and Washington. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
