<P>
Two Commodity Dealers Banned: Two former commodity futures salesmen at the 
Chicago Mercantile Exchange were each fined $150,000 and permanently barred 
from the exchange for fraud, the CME said. Norman Furlett and Ira Greenspon 
were accused of a scheme to divert customers' profits into their own accounts. 
They had worked at GNP Commodities Inc. The CME said the two have repaid 
customers an unspecified amount. 
