<TEXT>
<P>
Layoffs at CBS News: CBS News is abolishing about 50 positions in a 
cost-cutting move. 
</P>
<P>
Some of the affected employees will be offered other jobs within the company, 
while a number have already left, a spokesman said. CBS News, which once 
employed more than 1,300, now numbers about 1,050. Middle East coverage will 
push the division about $25 million to $30 million over budget this year. The 
network this week is undergoing its annual budgeting process for the next 
fiscal year. 
</P>
