<P>
Saturn May Add More Models: General Motors Corp.'s highly touted subsidiary 
will expand from three to 10 models by 1994, an automotive journal reported. 
</P>
<P>
Automotive News said Saturn also may increase its plant capacity. The Spring 
Hill, Tenn., company will add a luxury sedan and coupe, a coupe convertible, 
two station wagons and two two-door hatchbacks in the next three years, the 
News said. The cars appear to be selling well. In fact, some dealers say they 
have a backlog of orders. 
