<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCKET LAUNCHES SECRET PAYLOAD INTO SPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Titan 4 rocket, the nation's most powerful unmanned launcher, blasted into 
space from Cape Canaveral Air Force Station with a secret military cargo Monday 
after a delay of nearly two months caused by unspecified technical problems. 
</P>
<P>
The Air Force would not divulge the nature of the payload, but civilian experts 
said they believed the rocket was carrying a $180-million satellite that could 
be used to instantly detect the launching of any Iraqi missiles against sites 
in the Middle East. 
</P>
