<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALARY INCREASES FOR CITY EMPLOYEES TAKE EFFECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA PARK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City employees received raises this month as the final installment of a 
three-year contract took effect. 
</P>
<P>
As negotiated in the original agreement, general employees received a 5% pay 
increase while raises for the Police and Fire departments were based on the 
median salaries of 10 Orange County cities. 
</P>
<P>
The average increase for Fire Department employees was 6% and the average for 
police was about 5%. 
</P>
<P>
Management personnel also received salary increases. Excluding department 
heads, a 2.5% increase was approved across the board with an option for an 
additional 2.5%. 
</P>
<P>
Keeping the police and fire employees' salaries in line with those of other 
cities was a major factor during negotiations, officials said. After many 
heated discussions, it was agreed to make adjustments according to the salaries 
other cities were paying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BUENA PARK (CA) -- GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES -- WAGES AND SALARIES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
