<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DENTAL OFFERS TO BUY 5 OF DHA'S 8 CLINICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CRISTINA LEE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHA Dental Inc., the operator of eight dental clinics in Orange, Los Angeles 
and Riverside counties now in Chapter 11 bankruptcy, said it has received an 
offer from Torrance-based Community Dental Services Inc. to purchase five of 
its clinics for $400,000. 
</P>
<P>
The five clinics are in Santa Ana, Anaheim, Costa Mesa, Covina and Bellflower. 
</P>
<P>
Not included are DHA clinics in Orange, Carson and Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
DHA has been soliciting bids for the clinics since July, three months after it 
filed a Chapter 11 bankruptcy petition because it was unable to pay $1.7 
million in federal and state taxes. Chapter 11 allows a company to continue 
operating while developing a plan to repay its debts and reorganize. 
</P>
<P>
"DHA is seeking court authorization to sell its eight clinics," said Robert 
Opera, an Irvine bankruptcy attorney representing DHA. 
</P>
<P>
An essential part of the agreement is to preserve the continuity of patient 
care, Opera said. 
</P>
<P>
"The prospective buyer, Community Dental Services, has agreed to continue 
treatment of existing DHA patients in all of the DHA clinics," he said. The 
company said it has about 10,000 patients at its clinics. 
</P>
<P>
Community Dental is affiliated with Smile Care Dental Group, also of Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, DHA listed sales of $20 million and debts of $17 million. The 
company's eight clinics currently employ about 60 dentists among its 300 
employees. 
</P>
<P>
Opera said the company would prefer to sell the clinics, if possible, to one or 
two buyers rather than piecemeal. 
</P>
<P>
"We're hopeful of preserving as many jobs as possible through the sale of the 
business rather than going through a liquidation of the assets," said Donald A. 
Patrick, DHA's acting chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
A hearing on the motion to sell the DHA clinics has been set for Nov. 21 in 
Santa Ana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
