<HEADLINE>
<P>
ISRAEL NOW USING GRAVEL-SHOOTER AGAINST ARABS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Israel has introduced a machine that fires lumps of gravel the size of eggs to 
disperse Palestinian demonstrators, military sources said today. 
</P>
<P>
It was designed especially for use against Palestinian demonstrators in the 
35-month-old intifada, a revolt against Israeli rule in the occupied West Bank 
and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
<P>
The sources said the device is not lethal and causes less harm than rubber and 
plastic bullets. 
</P>
<P>
Israel has been criticized for using lethal force against Palestinians. At 
least 738 Arabs have been killed by Israelis since the start of the Palestinian 
uprising in December, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
The gravel shooter can fire up to 600 lumps of gravel a minute over a distance 
of 75 yards, Israel radio said. 
</P>
<P>
An earlier gravel shooter proved ineffective at close range. 
</P>
</TEXT>
