<P>
AUTHOR CLANCY SEES END TO WAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OMAHA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Best-selling author Tom Clancy, whose "The Hunt for Red October" and other 
thrillers are noted for their detail of military technology and combat 
maneuvers, says an end to war is desirable and possible. 
</P>
<P>
"There's no law of God or nature that says we have to have a conflict 
anywhere," Clancy said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
He is in Omaha through today to speak at a benefit for the Greater Omaha 
Chamber of Commerce and the Omaha Public Library Foundation. He is also 
scheduled to tour Strategic Air Command headquarters with Gen. John T. Chain, 
the SAC commander, as his guide. 
</P>
<P>
Known for being publicity-shy, he reportedly consented to the visit at the 
urging of Chamber of Commerce President Bob Bell, a retired Navy vice admiral 
he met at the Pentagon. 
</P>
<P>
"I got hustled very skillfully," he said. "I don't mean to seem ungracious, but 
I have four kids. I'm just domestic, I'm sorry. I think there were two weeks in 
this year I didn't have to leave home for something." 
</P>
